    <br />

    
    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Role of handheld mobile devices in large scale information gathering process in indian scenario(s)</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Lukose, Rohan k<br />jaiswal, Raju kumar</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Role of handheld mobile devices<br />information gathering process in indian scenario(s)</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6091</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">This project aims to explore various scenarios, and develop applications to realize the same, where mobile devices act as information providers. This application collects information regarding traffic and road conditions, accidents and other such incidents, public infrastructure status etc. from the users of this application. Hence, the complexity of the application on the handheld is lesser compared to the complexity at the information processing at the server. The major areas of interest of this application are:- (1) Accidents and Incidents, (2) Traffic and Road Conditions, (3)Public Infrastructure and (4)CommuniTwitter. Accident and Critical injuries can happen at any time. This application tends to simplify the complexity of reporting an incident by tracing the location of user by GPS coordinates and reporting it to the nearest help center. The user will get this information by the correlation of data sent by other users and also with the help of other traffic monitoring resources. The user can inform the concerned government authorities about the social issues of their locality (road conditions, drainage, electricity, water, garbage problems, etc.) through this application. This application would direct the report to server, which will automatically process the report and forward it to the concerned authorities nearby user's area with the help of GPS coordinates of the user or through network provider in form of a text messages. CommuniTwitter aims at creation of twitter like social community in which groups are formed and survey regarding a common topic can be conducted. Group messaging is supported through sms/gprs</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17391">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17391</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/17018">CSE-2013</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
